<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Dibi database layer has very usefull feature which can fetch tree array from DB according special grouping string.</p>

<p>Here is API doc:
<a href="http://api.dibiphp.com/dibi/DibiResult.html#methodfetchAssoc">http://api.dibiphp.com/dibi/DibiResult.html/…</a></p>

<p>You only set somethink like this "assoc1,#,assoc2,=,assoc3,@"
assoc1-3 are table colums.</p>

<p>And method result this array:
$data[assoc1][index][assoc2]['assoc3']-&gt;value = {record}</p>

<p>Source code is here:
<a href="http://code.google.com/p/dibi/source/browse/trunk/dibi/libs/DibiResult.php">http://code.google.com/p/dibi/…</a></p>

<p>This is great for grouping data, tree list (discussion), etc.</p>

<p>Zend_DB already has fetchAssoc metohd, but better name for this method is fetchTree, or somethink else.</p>

